author: Fatin Nabila Kamarol Zaman
text: Fast forward to 21 years later, Alhamdulillah they’re still here. But in between of that 21 years...someone else died. It was so sudden and took me exactly 8 years to properly let go.

author: Fatin Nabila Kamarol Zaman
text: I couldn’t help it but crying almost everyday. Praying & praying each and everyday so that both of them would stay longer cause I was only 9 and wasn’t ready for such test. Mentally and physically.

author: Fatin Nabila Kamarol Zaman
text:
So, take care & don’t make urself hated. 

And hearing this made me so devastated anddd

author: Fatin Nabila Kamarol Zaman
text: She started telling me ‘you don’t have siblings’. Imagine how lonely would you be if we (parents) could no longer be with you. Guess, If i’m no longer around, to whom you’re going to rely on?

author: Fatin Nabila Kamarol Zaman
text: This of course reminded me so much of my younger self, when I was 9, my mom suddenly fell ill, that we thought she wasn’t going to make it. She then started telling me, that I had to take care of myself, ringan tulang helping the saudara doing house chores...

author: Fatin Nabila Kamarol Zaman
text: It’s been 8 years we’ve known each other & tbh I have witnessed most of their vulnerabilities each & everytime. But unaware of their actual miseries in details. And..

author: Fatin Nabila Kamarol Zaman
text: My friends for the first time opened up on how emotionally affected they were, about their moms’ passing & recently one of their only sibling diagnosed with yet to be known cysts
